# CodeGuild MVP — Walkthrough

## What Was Built

A full **monorepo** at `/media/adi/New Volume/Projects/CodeGuild` with three independent services:

```
CodeGuild/
├── README.md
├── backend-core/     ← Express + Firebase Admin (port 3001)
├── backend-ai/       ← Express + Gemini API (port 3002)
└── frontend/         ← Next.js App Router + Tailwind (port 3000)
```

---

## Backend-Core

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `index.js` | Express entry, Firebase Admin init, CORS, route mount |
| `config/ranks.js` | 5 rank tiers (Novice → Master) + helper fns |
| `config/scoring.js` | Score → exp multiplier (100%/75%/50%/0%) |
| `data/quests.json` | 5 hardcoded quests across ranks 1–4 |
| `routes/users.js` | `POST /api/users/init` + `GET /api/users/:id` |
| `routes/quests.js` | `GET /api/quests` with `?rank=` filter |
| `routes/submit.js` | `POST /api/submit` → calls AI → writes Firestore |

## Backend-AI

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `index.js` | Express entry, CORS |
| `routes/evaluate.js` | `POST /api/evaluate` → Gemini `gemini-1.5-flash` → JSON parse with retry |

## Frontend Scenes

| Scene | File | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| Login | `scenes/LoginScene.tsx` | Town background, pixel card, Google Sign-In |
| Town | `scenes/TownScene.tsx` | Map background + guild hall overlay + pulsing hotspot |
| Guild Interior | `scenes/GuildInteriorScene.tsx` | Interior bg + 2 hotspots (receptionist modal / quest board) |
| Quest Board | `scenes/QuestBoardScene.tsx` | Wooden noticeboard UI, quest cards grid, rank filter |
| Submission | `scenes/SubmissionScene.tsx` | Code textarea, evaluating state, result panel |

**Shared components:** `HUD.tsx` (persistent rank/exp overlay), `LoadingScreen.tsx` (1.5s black transition)

